topic.title: Access Control Services (ACS)

body.p: Switchtec P2Ps support Access Control Services (ACS) as defined in PCIe Base Specification Revision 4.0. ACS checks are performed by the PCI-to-PCI bridge function. ACS applies to ports operating in the following modes:

li.p: Upstream Switch Port (USP) with Management EP
ACS cannot be used partitions that have a a vRC (PSX)
ACS is not supported when using NTB (PSX/PFX)

body.p: The following DSP ACS capabilities are supported:
The following USP ACS capabilities are supported:

The PCI-to-PCI bridge function only applies ACS checks to TLPs flowing in the upstream direction. For a DSP, these are TLPs that are received from the port's link, regardless of the final destination of the TLP (e.g., regardless of whether the TLP is going to the upstream port or a peer downstream switch port). For a multi-function upstream port, these are TLPs received by the PCI-to-PCI bridge function on its secondary side.
TLP types and supported ACS controls are listed in Table 1

li.p: ACS B and ACS T are not supported for Message since AT field is reserved in Message
ACS checks for AtomicOps Requests are same as Memory Requests
ACS is not applied for VGA Memory Request since VGA Memory Request flows downstream
